1 Section 1. NRS 174.031 is hereby amended to read as follows:
2 174.031 1. At the arraignment of a defendant in justice court
3 or municipal court, but before the entry of a plea, the court may
4 determine whether the defendant is eligible for assignment to a
5 preprosecution diversion program established pursuant to NRS
6 174.032. The court shall receive input from the prosecuting attorney
7 and the attorney for the defendant, if any, whether the defendant
8 would benefit from and is eligible for assignment to the program.
9 2. A defendant may be determined to be eligible by the court
10 for assignment to a preprosecution diversion program if the
11 defendant:
12 (a) Is charged with a misdemeanor other than:
13 (1) A crime of violence;
14 (2) Vehicular manslaughter as described in NRS 484B.657;
15 (3) Driving under the influence of intoxicating liquor or a
16 controlled substance in violation of NRS 484C.110, 484C.120 or
17 484C.130; or
18 (4) A minor traffic offense; and
19 (b) Has not previously been [:
20 (1) Convicted of violating any criminal law other than a
21 minor traffic offense; or
22 (2) Ordered by a court to complete a preprosecution
23 diversion program in this State.] convicted of:
24 (1) A crime of violence;
25 (2) A sexual offense as defined in NRS 202.876;
26 (3) A crime of battery which constitutes domestic violence
27 pursuant to NRS 200.485;
28 (4) Vehicular manslaughter as described in NRS 484B.657;
29 or
30 (5) Driving under the influence of intoxicating liquor or a
31 controlled substance in violation of NRS 484C.110, 484C.120 or
32 484C.130.
33 3. If a defendant is determined to be eligible for assignment to
34 a preprosecution diversion program pursuant to subsection 2, the
35 justice court or municipal court may order the defendant to complete
36 the program pursuant to subsection 5 of NRS 174.032.
37 4. A defendant has no right to complete a preprosecution
38 diversion program or to appeal the decision of the justice court or
39 municipal court relating to the participation of the defendant in such
40 a program.
